column1: # The reading for March 1913 is part estimated and has been retained.
# The reading for May 1945 is an estimate and has been omitted.
# The readings for January-March 1947 are part estimates for snow and have been retained.
# The reading for August 1951 is an estimate and has been omitted.
# The gauge was moved 33 yards north on November 5 1948. (Easy to mis-read this as 533 yards.)
# The station continued until 1964 according to MIDAS.
